  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Migrating to octopress and Jekyll]]></title>
    <link href="http://nikvdp.github.com/blog/2013/06/09/migrating-to-octopress-and-jekyll/"/>
    <updated>2013-06-09T18:43:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://nikvdp.github.com/blog/2013/06/09/migrating-to-octopress-and-jekyll</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Wordpress has a lot of good points. It&rsquo;s plugin system is flexible and powerful, and this has made it extendable to the point where I can tolerate using it. For example, I can write my posts in markdown and have them automatically end up in HTML.</p>

<p>Unfortunately, to support all this cool stuff wordpress has become bloated. I want to be able to write a post and toss it online in seconds, without thinking about it. Wordpress loadtimes kill, 1 or more seconds for a pageload, and adding a new post requires 3 or 4 clicks, so a simple post ends up taking > 30 seconds to get online. Plus, there&rsquo;s no offline support, and while plugins make markdown usable it&rsquo;s still a bit ugly.</p>

<p>Not acceptable.</p>

<p>So, let&rsquo;s try Jekyll. Setting it up was a lot more difficult than I had originally thought. But it is working.</p>
]]></content>
